Friday, November 8, 2013

Friday Fun Fact

   The rod of Asclepius is an Ancient Greek symbol associated with
   astrology and with healing the sick through medicine. It consists of a
   serpent entwined around a staff. Asclepius, the son of Apollo, was
   practitioner of medicine in Ancient Greek mythology.
   This is a great picture! Symbolizing the use of healthy foods as
   "medicine".
   [blogger-image--1591429728.jpg]
